theorem isOpen_of_closed_and_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hClosed : IsClosed A) (hP3 : Topology.P3 A) : IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  -- From `P3`, and the fact that `A` is closed, obtain `A ⊆ interior A`.
  have hSub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
    simpa [hClosed.closure_eq] using hP3
  -- Combine with the trivial inclusion `interior A ⊆ A` to get equality.
  have hEq : interior A = A := by
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm interior_subset hSub
  -- Use the characterization of open sets via their interior.
  simpa [hEq] using (isOpen_iff_interior_eq).2 hEq
